HEADWORD: Silicified
<hw>Si*lic"i*fied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Combined or impregnated with silicon or silica, especially the
latter; <as>as, <ex>silicified</ex> wood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

